    "recap_url": "https://www.SMCGaels.com/news/2026/3/10/baseball-bsb-saint-marys-fall-in-7-innings-to-uc-santa-barbara",
    "recap_headline": "Saint Mary's College of California",
    "recap_text": "SANTA BARBARA, Calif.\n\u2013 The Saint Mary's baseball team rattled off ten hits through seven innings but fell in run-rule fashion, 13-3 to UC Santa Barbara Tuesday night.\nThe Gaels got within a run in the third inning after an RBI double from\nJacob Johnson\n, but the Gauchos scored four in the bottom half of the third and recorded another five-run inning in the sixth to seal the ten-run victory.\nSophomore catcher\nIan Armstrong\nreturned behind the plate for Saint Mary's and went 3-for-3 with the bat including a run scored and his first triple of the season.\nBrady Petit\nand\nCody Kashimoto\nwere the other two players with multiple hits in the game while\nJacob Johnson\nand\nDario Freschi\nhad the two RBI hits for Saint Mary's.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nTrue freshman\nJake Nobles\nmade his third start of the season and got into the third but couldn't finish the inning. Three of the four runs would get charged to the freshman as he took his first loss of the season.\nUC Santa Barbara hit a two-out three-run homer in the first, but Saint Mary's responded with runs in the second and third inning. Right fielder\nDiego Castellanos\nreached base with a single to start the second and came around to score on a wild pitch to get the Gaels on the board. In the third, Saint Mary's put two runners on again and this time\nJacob Johnson\ncashed in with a two-out double down the left field line to score\nTanner Griffith\nand put the Gaels within a run.\nThe momentum would be short lived for the Gaels though as Santa Barbara put up four runs in the bottom of the third and then a five-spot in the sixth to put the game away. The Gauchos bumped Nobles from the game in the third and went on to get a pair of RBI doubles to contribute to the four-run inning.\nThe Gaels got one back to start the sixth thanks to a leadoff triple off the center field wall from Armstrong and then freshman\nDario Freschi\nwould deliver a pinch-hit RBI single the next at bat to make it 8-3. The Gauchos took firm control of the game though with five more runs in the bottom half of the sixth to put them within run-rule range. The Gaels would go down in order in the seventh to end the game 13-3.\nSaint Mary's had more hits than UC Santa Barbara going into the sixth inning but the difference at the plate came with runners on and in scoring position. The Gauchos hit .500 in both categories while the Gaels were .267 from the plate with runners on and just .182 with runners in scoring position.\nRedshirt sophomore\nFinn Chapman\ncompleted two full innings after the departure of Nobles and led all SMC pitchers with four strikeouts, allowing just two runs off one hit.\nGAME NOTES\nSaint Mary's had ten hits on the night for its 12th game this season with double-digit hits\nArmstrong matched his season high with three hits in the ballgame\nArmstrong's triple in the sixth inning went down as his first of the season and fourth of his career\nFinn Chapman\nrecorded a career high four strikeouts\nPetit recorded his sixth multi-hit game of the season\nKashimoto went 2-for-3 from the plate to extend his hit streak to nine games\nCastellanos also had a hit in Tuesday's game and now leads the team with a current 10-game hit streak\nLOOKING AHEAD\nSaint Mary's will head to Arizona this weekend for a round robin featuring four games against Grand Canyon and Rice starting on Friday, March 13. Additional game information can be found at smcgaels.com.\nBe sure to follow your Gaels on Facebook, Instagram, and X to get all the latest Saint Mary's athletics updates and information.\n#GaelsRise"
  },
